1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on the need for new tools to reinforce trust and security through the Internet, and proposes an improved generator based on chaotic iterations for use in Internet security. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the quality of pseudo-random number generators and their importance in various cryptosystems and data hiding schemes, which is a topic related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an improved generator based on chaotic iterations, which is a topic related to systems and control. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of the proposed generator in the context of Internet security, which is a topic related to networking and Internet architecture. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper compares various generators and presents statistical results, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms.
